entities.description: The proportion of individuals within a population who exhibit a particular characteristic or behavior at a specific time.
A procedure in SUDAAN used to generate estimates and tests of differences for prevalence data.
Prevalence estimates differentiated based on gender, such as males and females.
The test statistic for the difference in means.
The p-value associated with the test statistic, indicating the significance of the difference.
The average value of a variable in the dataset.
The standard error of the mean.
A range of values derived from sample data that is likely to contain the true population parameter.
The interval within which the true mean is expected to lie with 95% confidence.

relationships.description: Relates the testing of differences to the SUDAAN procedure used.
Indicates that the PROC DESCRIPT procedure generates prevalence estimates.
Indicates that the prevalence estimate can be gender-specific.
Indicates the t-statistic used in the test of differences.
Indicates the p-value for the test statistic.
Indicates that PROC DESCRIPT produces mean values.
Relates the mean to its standard error.
Indicates that PROC DESCRIPT calculates confidence intervals.
Indicates that the confidence interval is calculated with 95% confidence.
